Luis Terrazas-Salgado

Bio

Luis Terrazas-Salgado is a PhD candidate at the Research Center in Food and Development in Mazatln, Sinaloa, Mexico. He studies the effects of xenobiotics on endocrine, embryonic and epigenomic disruption in zebrafish.

My research use a zebrafish, to characterize molecular mechanisms underpinning potential impacts of xenobiotics on human and animal health.

Education

Center for Research in Food and Development | Mazatlan, Sin, Mexico

Ph.D.candidate in Environmental Management | August 2018 - Present

Polytechnic University of Sinaloa | Mazatlan, Sin, Mexico

M.S. in Biotechnology and Molecular Genetics | September 2015 - Aug 2017

Polytechnic University of Sinaloa | Mazatlan, Sin, Mexico

B.S. Biotechnology Engineering | September 2011 - Jen 2015

Interests

  • Zebrafish
  • Ecotoxicology
  • Epigenetics
  • Photography
